\begin_layout Section
Oncodrive
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Oncodrive is a method to identify driver alterations in a matrix of genes
 altered over a number of samples.
 We assume that the genes that are altered in more samples than expected
 by chance are those that contribute the most to the cancerous phenotype
 and are therefore driver alterations (See 
\begin_inset CommandInset href
LatexCommand href
name "Gundem et al., Nature Methods, 2010"
target "http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/20111033"

\end_inset

 for more information).
\end_layout

